# Figma MCP — design-to-code workflow

Source file: [Prestige Cakes (Copy)](https://www.figma.com/design/Z4LCqR1wz1hsXOUUo1FeAX/Prestige-Cakes--Copy-) (`fileKey: Z4LCqR1wz1hsXOUUo1FeAX`)

Discovery inventory: `docs/figma-discovery.md`  
Design tokens: `docs/figma-tokens.css`

## Before implementing any screen

1. Look up the frame **nodeId** in `docs/figma-discovery.md`.
2. Call `get_design_context` with `fileKey` + `nodeId`.
3. If the response is sparse/truncated, split into child sections (see homepage section table) and call again per section.
4. Call `get_screenshot` on the same nodeId for visual reference.
5. Use asset URLs from the MCP response — do not substitute placeholder icons or images.

## Code adaptation rules

- Treat `get_design_context` output as **structure reference**, not final code style.
- Map colors to CSS variables in `docs/figma-tokens.css` — no hardcoded hex when a token exists.
- Reuse shared layout from header frame `2018:685` across all public pages.
- Prefer Server Components; add `"use client"` only for cart, forms, modals, and language selector.
- Romanian copy comes from Figma text layers — preserve exact strings.

## Rate limits

Figma MCP read tools have per-plan limits. Batch work per screen; use `get_metadata` for cheap discovery. See [Figma MCP rate limits](https://developers.figma.com/docs/figma-mcp-server/).

## Build order

1. Layout shell (header `2018:685`)
2. Homepage sections (`2007:162` children)
3. Catalog pages (Vitrină live, produse la comandă, product detail)
4. Cart → checkout → confirmation
5. Admin dashboard screens

## Convex wiring

Derive schema from checkout/order frames (`2361:*`, `2450:*`, `2458:*`). Queries in server components; mutations in client forms.
